{"title": "Scent organ development in Creatonotos moths: regulation by pyrrolizidine alkaloids", "url": "https://science.sciencemag.org/content/215/4537/1264.short", "author": "D Schneider and M Boppr\u00e9 and J Zweig and SB Horsley\u2026", "abstract": "7-Hydroxy-6, 7-dihydro-5H-pyrolizine-1-carboxaldehyde is the major volatile component of the scent organs in males of two species of Creatonotos (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae). The biosynthesis of this presumed pheromone depends on the presence of pyrrolizidine \u2026"}